  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc1\u0ddd\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Approval to amend the Sri Lanka Freedom Party constitution",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The approval of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party's All Sri Lanka Committee to amend the constitution was also received today (2).",
        "The party's 71st anniversary celebration and the All Ceylon committee meeting was held today (2) at the Maharagama Youth Service Council Auditorium under the chairmanship of the party chairman, former president Mr. Maithripala Sirisena, where this approval was received.",
        "Party Senior Vice Presidents representing the All Ceylon Committee, Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva, Minister Mahinda Amaraweera, Party National Organizer Duminda Dissanayake, Treasurer Lasantha Alagiyawanna, Members of Parliament Chamara Sampath Dasanayake and Jagath Pushpakumara were also present. But they abstained from voting in the polls held to adopt the constitutional amendments.",
        "Party Secretary General Member of Parliament Mr. Dayasiri Jayasekara presented the new constitutional amendment to the All Ceylon Committee, including increasing the number of party senior vice presidents from 4 to 7, vice presidents from 10 to 14, and authorizing the party president to appoint not more than 35 members to the party executive council. did",
        "Also giving the chairman the power to remove the officers appointed to the positions at the discretion of the chairman, if the Central Committee decides that an officer is not fulfilling the responsibilities of the position in a proper manner, transfer those responsibilities to another officer of the executive council with immediate effect, ending disciplinary actions against a party member or organization. The new amendments also include clauses such as suspending their membership and activities, temporarily suspending the membership of the party in cases where the chairman is convinced that any member is doing undisciplined activities against the party's constitution and policies and suspending the party's membership or expelling the party after the relevant measures.",
        "After the secretary presented this amendment to the council, when the party chairman, former president Mr. Maithripala Sirisena came to the stage and asked the party members to raise their hands, everyone raised their hands except for the above-mentioned people, and no one raised their hands against it.",
        "Accordingly, Mr. Maithripala Sirisena announced to the assembly that the new constitution will be passed as there are no opponents to the proposal.",
        "When these amendments were presented to the party central committee meeting held yesterday (1) at the party headquarters, the above six abstained from voting on it, and they had said that these amendments were made to increase the power of the party chairman."
      ],
